2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20don't%20realize%20how%20expensive%20everything%20you%20own%20is%20until%20something%20like%20this%20happens.%20I%20was%20completely%20overwhelmed%20by%20the%20financial%20cost%20of%20replacing%20my%20furniture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20earning%20peanuts%20at%20the%20time%20and%20only%20got%20%C2%A32%2C000%20(%242%2C500)%20of%20insurance%20even%20though%20it%20was%20worth%20far%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20friend%20of%20a%20friend%20gave%20me%20a%20bed%2C%20a%20mattress%2C%20and%20a%20sofa%2C%20which%20was%20invaluable.%20Then%20I%20just%20headed%20to%20the%20secondhand%20store%20across%20the%20road%20from%20my%20apartment%20and%20had%20to%20buy%20basically%20everything%20in%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222048%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Helen%20Chandler-Wilde%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6620feff20b15f0ff4290b4c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221536%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHelen%20Chandler-Wilde's%20book%20%26quot%3BLost%20%26amp%3B%20Found%26quot%3B%20explores%20why%20we%20buy%20and%20hold%20on%20to%20things..%3Cp%3EHelen%20Chandler-Wilde%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20bought%20a%20dining%20table%2C%20plates%20and%20crockery%2C%20some%20rickety%20chairs%2C%20and%20a%20mirror%20%E2%80%94%20turns%20out%20you%20really%20need%20one%20for%20getting%20dressed%20in%20the%20morning%20before%20work!%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20no%20time%20to%20browse%3B%20I%20just%20needed%20to%20have%20the%20bare%20necessities%20that%20I%20could%20afford.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHaving%20stuff%20doesn't%20make%20you%20happier%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fire%20has%20reframed%20my%20way%20of%20thinking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20definitely%20have%20less%20now%20than%20I%20did%20before.%20That's%20partly%20because%20I%20feel%20like%20my%20belongings%20could%20go%20at%20any%20point%2C%20so%20I%20don't%20trust%20owning%20stuff%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20truthfully%2C%20I%20can't%20even%20remember%20some%20of%20the%20belongings%20that%20were%20in%20the%20storage%20unit%2C%20which%20shows%20how%20they%20didn't%20actually%20benefit%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20learned%20not%20to%20get%20attached%20to%20physical%20objects.%20Beyond%20the%20basics%2C%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20stuff%20doesn't%20actually%20make%20you%20happier.%20Now%20I%20prefer%20spending%20money%20on%20going%20out%20for%20dinner%20with%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20advantages%20to%20not%20having%20so%20many%20things.%20It's%20easy%20to%20keep%20clean%2C%20and%20there's%20less%20stress%20associated%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20dangerous%20cycle%20of%20thinking%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20really%20tricky%20for%20me%20now%20to%20have%20conversations%20with%20friends%20about%20shopping%20because%20their%20ideas%20are%20so%20different.%20I%20find%20it%20challenging%20when%20people%20say%2C%20%26quot%3B%20Oh%2C%20I%20really%20need%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20always%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20you%20might%20want%20it%2C%20but%20you%20definitely%20don't%20need%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221052%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Helen%20Chandler-Wilde%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66210bf020b15f0ff4290c9b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221698%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHelen%20explored%20why%20%3Cp%3EHelen%20Chandler-Wilde%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20generation%20spends%20more%20time%20alone%20and%20looking%20at%20ads%2C%20and%20that%20has%20an%20impact%20on%20how%20we%20see%20the%20world.%20It's%20become%20a%20default%20state%20to%20look%20at%20what%20others%20have%20and%20want%20it%20yourself.%20People%20browse%20constantly%20on%20Instagram%20or%20social%20media%20and%20convince%20themselves%20that%20they%20won't%20be%20happy%20unless%20they%20buy%20certain%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20that's%20not%20true%20at%20all.%20Your%20life%20will%20be%20perfectly%20fine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20loop%20you%20can%20get%20stuck%20in%2C%20but%20as%20soon%20as%20you%20stop%20browsing%2C%20you%20stop%20wanting%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EObviously%2C%20there%20are%20people%20who%20don't%20have%20everything%20they%20need%2C%20and%20that's%20completely%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWork%20out%20what%20you%20need%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20judgmental%20at%20all%20about%20how%20much%20people%20own%2C%20and%20I'm%20not%20a%20minimalist%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20I%20think%20is%20important%20is%20to%20work%20out%20what%20you%20need%20for%20yourself%2C%20not%20copy%20what%20everyone%20else%20has.%20Reconsider%20how%20much%20you%20buy%20and%20%3Cem%3Ewhy%3C%2Fem%3E%20you%20buy%20what%20you%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20about%20selecting%20the%20things%20that%20actually%20have%20value%20in%20your%20life%20and%20are%20worth%20the%20space%20in%20your%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20me%2C%20memories%20make%20you%20who%20you%20are.%20So%2C%20I%20have%20lots%20of%20pictures%20on%20the%20walls%20of%20my%20house%3B%20it's%20cozy%20and%20creates%20a%20sense%20of%20space.%20And%2C%20though%20I%20definitely%20do%20still%20keep%20those%20sentimental%20things%2C%20I%20have%20tried%20to%20pare%20them%20back%20a%20bit%20because%20anything%20can%20become%20sentimental%20if%20you%20let%20it.%20Having%20one%20amazing%20picture%20of%20your%20best%20friend's%20wedding%20is%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20focus%20on%20the%20good%20things%2C%20you%20understand%20that%20you%20most%20likely%20already%20have%20everything%20you%20already%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHelen%20Chandler-Wilde's%20book%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.octopusbooks.co.uk%2Ftitles%2Fhelen-chandler-wilde%2Flost-found%2F9781783255573%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELost%20%26amp%3B%20Found%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%20was%20published%20in%20March.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ER