0noticed%20distinct%20differences%20in%20approach.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3ESchool%20was%20low-stress%20in%20the%20Netherlands%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhere%20we%20lived%20in%20the%20Netherlands%2C%20children%20as%20young%20as%20four%20years%20old%20often%20happily%20walked%20themselves%20to%20school.%20The%20school%20my%20son%20attended%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20was%20run%20like%20a%20well-oiled%20machine%2C%20yet%20they%20still%20maintained%20a%20playful%20and%20innocent%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20school%20administrators%20were%20strict%20about%20timeliness%20%E2%80%94%20I%20often%20witnessed%20that%20if%20students%20arrived%20even%20one%20minute%20late%2C%20they%20were%20considered%20late%2C%20with%20no%20exceptions.%20However%2C%20discipline%20for%20kids%20was%20simply%20a%20stern%20talking-to%20from%20teachers.%20Teachers%20told%20us%20that%20if%20children%20had%20issues%20with%20each%20other%2C%20they%20were%20expected%20to%20sort%20it%20amongst%20themselves%2C%20while%20the%20adults%20observed%20from%20a%20distance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFriends%20who%20had%20kids%20at%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-vs-uk-school-writing-styles-education-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eother%20schools%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20confirmed%20that%20this%20focus%20on%20independent%20conflict%20resolution%20with%20minimal%20adult%20intervention%20was%20common.%20Play%20was%20the%20central%20focus%20of%20the%20day%20for%20children%20until%20they%20were%20about%20seven%20years%20old.%20The%20primary%20focus%20during%20those%20early%20years%20was%20on%20children%20learning%20to%20coexist%20with%20one%20another%20rather%20than%20academics.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELearning%20to%20swim%20was%20also%20a%20significant%20focus%20in%20the%20early%20years%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20and%20considered%20more%20critical%20than%20learning%20to%20read%20by%20many%20locals%20we%20spoke%20with.%20Once%20compulsory%2C%20now%20only%20some%20schools%20integrate%20swim%20classes%20into%20the%20curriculum.%20Given%20the%20numerous%20canals%20everywhere%2C%20this%20emphasis%20is%20understandable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChildren%20at%20my%20son's%20school%20spent%20a%20large%20portion%20of%20their%20day%20outdoors%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20weather%2C%20which%20parents%20said%20was%20typical.%20The%20Dutch%20often%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20bad%20weather%2C%20only%20bad%20clothing.%26quot%3B%20At%20school%2C%20my%20son%20assisted%20in%20preparing%20daily%20vegan%20meals%2C%20and%20occasionally%20brought%20home%20crafts%20to%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFriends%20who%20had%20older%20kids%20in%20the%20Netherlands%20told%20me%20that%20the%20homework%20increased%20once%20they%20hit%20middle%20school%2C%20where%20there%20was%20more%20of%20an%20emphasis%20on%20academics.%20I%20truly%20appreciated%20this%20low-stress%20setting%20we%20encountered%20during%20our%20son's%20primary%20school%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lana%20Katsaros%20with%20her%20son%20and%20husband.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6622be0423b29110d3011733%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELana%20Katsaros%20says%20that%20homeschooling%20allows%20her%20family%20to%20travel%20without%20worrying%20her%20son%20will%20miss%20schoolwork.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20Lana%20Katsaros%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20saw%20more%20emphasis%20on%20collaboration%20than%20individual%20performance%20in%20Portugal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Portugal%2C%20there%20was%20an%20emphasis%20on%20projects%20that%20children%20completed%20together%20to%20enhance%20their%20collaboration%20skills%2C%20and%20praise%20was%20often%20based%20on%20the%20collaboration%20itself%20rather%20than%20individual%20performance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20noticed%20that%20children%20rarely%20had%20packed%20schedules%20filled%20with%20extracurricular%20activities%20like%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20often%20stayed%20up%20very%20late%20at%20night%20with%20their%20families%2C%20based%20on%20our%20own%20observations%20and%20talking%20to%20Portuguese%20parents.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20I%20adored%20the%20genuinely%20%26quot%3Bcrunchy%26quot%3B%20vibe%20of%20the%20schools%20my%20son%20attended%20and%20the%20kindness%20of%20the%20teachers%2C%20I%20believed%20our%20son%20would%20benefit%20from%20more%20structure%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fmorning-routine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Econsistency%20in%20his%20routine%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20So%2C%20for%20a%20time%2C%20we%20supplemented%20even%20more%20than%20our%20usual%20load%20of%20schoolwork%20at%20home%20to%20provide%20more%20academic%20consistency%20during%20his%20short%20stint%20at%20a%20Portuguese%20school%20and%20eventually%20transitioned%20to%20only%20homeschooling%20again%20and%20met%20with%20a%20homeschool%20group%20for%20field%20trips.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20noticed%20less%20encouragement%20of%20competition%20in%20Italy%20than%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAt%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fliving-in-italy-key-differences-between-us-kindergarten-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eschool%20my%20son%20goes%20to%20in%20Italy%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20it%20was%20immediately%20evident%20that%20food%20and%20dining%20is%20treated%20as%20an%20important%20part%20of%20the%20school%20day.%20Students%20are%20given%20a%20proper%20dining%20experience%20with%20formal%20table%20settings.%20The%20primary%20schools%20get%20a%20full%20two-hour%20break%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20day%20including%20lunch%20and%20free%20time%2C%20known%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3Eriposo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20lending%20to%20a%20much%20longer%20school%20day%20overall.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFootball%20(soccer)%20is%20also%20taken%20seriously%2C%20so%20most%20schools%20we%20visited%20have%20specialized%20schedules%20specifically%20for%20children%20who%20play%20and%20perhaps%20want%20to%20pursue%20it%20as%20a%20career.%20Participation%20in%20the%20arts%2C%20football%2C%20and%20music%20is%20encouraged%2C%20but%20football%20is%20by%20far%20the%20most%20popular%20activity%20at%20our%20school%20and%20in%20our%20region.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20for%20the%20emphasis%20on%20the%20curriculum%2C%20so%20far%2C%20it%20seems%20far%20less%20rigid%20than%20in%20the%20US.%20Cognitive%20and%20social%20skills%20appear%20to%20be%20the%20primary%20objectives%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20heavy%20focus%20on%20testing.%20There%20is%20almost%20no%20encouragement%20of%20competition%20that%20we%20witnessed%2C%20as%20collaboration%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20focus%20until%20middle%20school.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20son%20is%20not%20yet%20in%20middle%20school%2C%20but%20from%20what%20I've%20heard%20both%20in%20preliminary%20conversations%20with%20schools%2C%20open%20days%2C%20and%20from%20Facebook%20groups%20with%20other%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraising-teenage-daughter-parenting-dubai-middle-east-difficult-spoiled-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexpat%20parents%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20it%20sounds%20like%20middle%20school%20takes%20a%20more%20rigorous%20academic%20approach%20across%20Europe.%20For%20example%2C%20some%20countries%2C%20like%20Italy%2C%20expect%20children%20to%20know%20their%20primary%20focus%20of%20study%20by%20the%20time%20they%20enter%20high%20school%2C%20and%20then%20are%20placed%20in%20a%20specialized%20school%20program%20geared%20towards%20that%20interest%20area.%20Middle%20school%20seems%20to%20help%20form%20this%20decision%20by%20focusing%20on%20more%20specific%20subjects%20like%20robotics%2C%20engineering%20and%20anatomy%2C%20as%20they%20are%20already%20expected%20to%20know%20how%20to%20work%20together.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20unifying%20theme%20we%20observed%20throughout%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-gen-zer-went-to-college-in-europe-not-america-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eschools%20in%20Europe%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20our%20son%20has%20attended%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20country%2C%20was%20to%20allow%20children%20to%20be%20children%20and%20let%20the%20serious%20learning%20come%20later.%20At%20almost%20all%20the%20schools%20my%20son%20attended%20or%20toured%2C%20more%20importance%20was%20placed%20on%20children's%20ability%20to%20coexist%20together%2C%20work%20on%20projects%20and%20tasks%20collaboratively%2C%20than%20on%20core%20subjects%20like%20math%2C%20science%2C%20and%20history%20in%20those%20early%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEach%20country%20had%20something%20we%20cherished%20and%20something%20we%20had%20to%20learn%20to%20adjust%20to.%20Overall%2C%20compared%20to%20our%20group%20homeschooling%20experience%20in%20the%20US%2C%20I%20would%20say%20that%20the%20primary%20schools%20in%20the%20European%20cities%20we%20joined%20were%20far%20less%20stressful.%20The%20academics%20seemed%20to%20get%20prioritized%20more%20as%20the%20kids%20got%20older.%20This%20makes%20me%20really%20appreciate%20how%20the%20lower%20grades%20focused%20on%20collaboration%20and%20coexistence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdifferences-europe-vs-us-primary-school-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713606121000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6622bb0623b29110d3011429%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdifferences-europe-vs-us-primary-school-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Our%20son%20is%20homeschooled%2C%20and%20as%20we%20travel%2C%20he%20joins%20classrooms.%20He's%20been%20to%20schools%20all%20over%20Europe%2C%20and%20they're%20different%20from%20schools%20in%20the%20US.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Lana%20Katsaros)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdifferences-europe-vs-us-primary-school-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Russian%20shelling%20kills%20one%20in%20Ukraine's%20north%20east%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713606116000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109456501%2Cimgsize-1525759.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Frussian-shelling-kills-one-in-ukraines-north-east%2Farticleshow%2F109456409.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F109456409.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EAn%20attack%20by%20Russian%20forces%20on%20two%20residential%20buildings%20in%20Ukraine's%20Kharkiv%20region%20resulted%20in%20the%20death%20of%20one%20person%20and%20the%20injury%20of%20another%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Vovchansk.%20The%20incident%20occurred%20near%20the%20Russian%20border%2C%20with%20the%20area%20frequently%20targeted%20during%20the%20ongoing%20conflict.%20A%2060-year-old%20woman%20sustained%20injuries%20in%20the%20assault%2C%20as%20depicted%20in%20a%20photo%20showing%20the