quot%3BBig%20Four%26quot%3B%20are%20the%20world's%20largest%20accounting%20firms.%20Here's%20how%20they%20compare%20in%20terms%20of%20pay%2C%20perks%2C%20and%20return-to-office%20policies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22gglover%40insider.com%20(George%20Glover)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeloitte-pwc-kpmg-ey-big-four-pay-perks-rto-policies-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Swiss%20environment%20minister%20plays%20down%20impact%20of%20European%20climate%20ruling%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713603682000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109455808%2Cimgsize-1533913.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fswiss-environment-minister-plays-down-impact-of-european-climate-ruling%2Farticleshow%2F109455639.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F109455639.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3ESwiss%20minister%20challenges%20European%20Court%20of%20Human%20Rights'%20climate%20change%20ruling%2C%20emphasizing%20inaction%20risks%20heatwaves.%20Swiss%20Federal%20Office%20of%20Justice%20must%20adhere%20to%20Council%20of%20Europe.%20Swiss%20People's%20Party%20opposes%2C%20citing%20referendum%20impact.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fswiss-environment-minister-plays-down-impact-of-european-climate-ruling%2Farticleshow%2F109455639.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fswiss-environment-minister-plays-down-impact-of-european-climate-ruling%2Famp_articleshow%2F109455639.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fswiss-environment-minister-plays-down-impact-of-european-climate-ruling%2Famp_articleshow%2F109455639.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China's%20latest%20supersonic%20spy%20drone%20looks%20a%20lot%20like%20the%20Lockheed%20D-21%20that%20crashed%20there%20in%201971%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lockheed%20engineers%20designed%20the%20D-21%20spy%20drone%20in%20the%201960s%20for%20reconnaissance%20missions%20too%20dangerous%20for%20piloted%20aircraft.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661ea92520b15f0ff4286109%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221178%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELockheed%20engineers%20designed%20the%20D-21%20spy%20drone%20in%20the%201960s%20for%20reconnaissance%20missions%20too%20dangerous%20for%20piloted%20aircraft.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ELockheed%20developed%20a%20spy%20drone%20in%20the%201960s%20that%20crashed%20in%20China.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EChina%20recently%20debuted%20a%20supersonic%20drone%20that%20bears%20a%20striking%20resemblance%20to%20Lockheed's%20D-21.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20D-21's%20urgent%20development%20was%20marked%20by%20ambition%20and%20tragedy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2020%2C%201971%2C%20a%20specially%20modified%20US%20Air%20Force%20B-52%20bomber%20from%20the%204200th%20Support%20Squadron%20took%20off%20from%20Andersen%20Air%20Force%20Base%20in%20Guam%20carrying%20a%20unique%20aircraft%20mounted%20under%20its%20wing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20aircraft%2C%20shaped%20like%20a%20dart%20and%20painted%20black%2C%20was%20a%20D-21%20supersonic%20reconnaissance%20drone.%20It%20was%20to%20be%20the%20fourth%20such%20drone%20to%20conduct%20aerial%20reconnaissance%20of%20China's%20Lop%20Nor%20nuclear%20test%20site%20in%20northwestern%20China%2C%20and%20despite%20its%20sophistication%2C%20it%20would%20crash%20into%20the%20very%20country%20it%20was%20intended%20to%20spy%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECreated%20by%20the%20renowned%20Lockheed%20Corporation%2C%20the%20D-21%20was%20the%20most%20advanced%20unmanned%20aircraft%20of%20its%20time.%20Intended%20to%20bridge%20a%20gap%20between%20burgeoning%20satellite%20technology%20and%20manned%20reconnaissance%20flights%2C%20the%20drone's%20development%20was%20filled%20with%20ambition%2C%20urgency%2C%20and%20tragedy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%20unsuccessful%2C%20the%20drone%20would%20be%20relegated%20to%20the%20annals%20of%20aviation%20history%20if%20not%20for%20the%20appearance%20of%20a%20strikingly%20similar%20Chinese%20drone%20unveiled%20at%20a%20recent%20military%20parade.%20This%20delta-shaped%20drone%20of%20similar%20size%20also%20requires%20being%20launched%20by%20a%20mothership.%20But%20Chinese%20engineers%20claim%20advances%20that%20go%20much%20farther%20than%20the%20D-21%2C%20reaching%2030%20miles%20into%20the%20atmosphere%20and%20speeds%20up%20to%20Mach%206.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20we%20know%20about%20the%20high-flying%20Chinese%20spy%20drone%20and%20the%20D-21%20upon%20which%20it%20could%20be%20based.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAn%20urgent%20need%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20origins%20of%20the%20D-21%20start%20in%201960%2C%20when%20Francis%20Gary%20Powers%20and%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fu2-dragon-lady-flying-over-60-years-but-plane-changed-2019-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EU-2%20spy%20plane%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20shot%20down%20over%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20by%20a%20Soviet%20surface-to-air%20missile.%20The%20incident%20pushed%20President%20Dwight%20Eisenhower%20to%20discontinue%20all%20manned%20reconnaissance%20flights%20over%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20to%20avoid%20future%20casualties%20and%20embarrassments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20need%20to%20surveil%20Soviet%20military%20sites%20was%20still%20vital%2C%20and%20while%20reconnaissance%20satellites%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nro.gov%2FAbout-NRO%2Fhistory%2Fhistory-corona%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estarting%20to%20be%20launched%20into%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20technology%20was%20nascent.%20Satellites%20carried%20a%20limited%20amount%20of%20film%20despite%20being%20in%20orbit%20for%20days%2C%20had%20limited%20repositioning%20ability%2C%20and%20were%20not%20as%20available%20for%20short-notice%20launches%20in%20emergencies%20compared%20to%20manned%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20faster%20and%20higher-flying%20successor%20to%20the%20U-2%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhistory-of-a-12-spy-plane-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA-12%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20in%20development.%20However%2C%20as%20a%20conventional%20aircraft%2C%20it%20still%20had%20to%20be%20manned%2C%20and%20the%20White%20House%20and%20CIA%20alike%20were%20both%20reluctant%20to%20risk%20the%20capture%20of%20another%20pilot%2C%20especially%20if%20it%20also%20meant%20losing%20an%20even%20more%20advanced%20aircraft%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20the%20CIA%20needed%20a%20stopgap%20solution%20until%20the%20satellite%20programs%20matured.%20In%201962%2C%20the%20Central%20Intelligence%20Agency%20approached%20Lockheed's%20Skunk%20Works%20division%20(which%20created%20the%20U-2%20and%20the%20A-12)%20for%20such%20a%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHigh%20altitude%2C%20high%20speed%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELockheed's%20solution%20was%20to%20create%20an%20unmanned%20high-altitude%20high-speed%20reconnaissance%20aircraft%20with%20similar%20capabilities%20as%20the%20A-12%2C%20but%20much%20smaller.%20Originally%20designated%20as%20the%20Q-12%2C%20the%20drone%20utilized%20a%20delta%20wing%20design%2C%20had%20a%20wingspan%20of%2019%20feet%2C%20and%20measured%2042%20feet%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20powered%20by%20a%20Marquardt%20RJ43-MA-20S4%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grc.nasa.gov%2Fwww%2Fk-12%2Fairplane%2Framjet.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eramjet%20engine%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20ran%20the%20entire%20length%20of%20the%20aircraft.%20Capable%20of%20producing%2011%2C500%20lbs.%20of%20thrust%2C%20the%20engine%20gave%20the%20drone%20a%20top%20speed%20of%20Mach%203.3%2C%20and%20enabled%20it%20to%20reach%20an%20altitude%20of%2095%2C000%20feet.%20The%20D-21's%20range%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20was%20over%203%2C000%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20it%20was%20powered%20by%20a%20ramjet%20engine%2C%20the%20drone%20had%20to%20be%20launched%20from%20a%20mothership%20once%20it%20reached%20a%20speed%20where%20the%20ramjet%20could%20be%20activated.%20A%20modified%20A-12%20was%20judged%20to%20be%20the%20best%20candidate.%20Redesignated%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fairandspace.si.edu%2Fmultimedia-gallery%2Fm-21-aircraft%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EM-21%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20jet%20would%20carry%20the%20drone%2C%20redesignated%20as%20the%20D-21%2C%20on%20its%20fuselage%2C%20then%20release%20it%20once%20it%20reached%20a%20speed%20where%20the%20ramjet%20could%20be%20activated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20released%2C%20the%20D-21%20would%20fly%20a%20pre-programmed%20route%20utilizing%20an%20internal%20navigation%20system%20to%20the%20area%20of%20interest%2C%20where%20it%20would%20take%20photos.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20taken%2C%20the%20D-21%20would%20fly%20to%20a%20designated%20area%2C%20eject%20its%20film%20cannister%2C%20then%20self-destruct.%20The%20film%20cannister%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20would%20be%20snatched%20from%20the%20sky%20as%20it%20parachuted%20down%20by%20a%20waiting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.key.aero%2Farticle%2Fcatch-falling-star%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJC-130B%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20be%20collected%20by%20a%20Navy%20vessel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDubbed%20Project%20Tagboard%2C%20the%20first%20carry%20test%20occurred%20on%20December%2022%2C%201964%2C%20with%20the%20first%20separation%20and%20flight%20test%20occurring%20on%20March%206%2C%201966.%20Two%20more%20largely%20successful%20tests%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20fourth%20flight%20test%2C%20on%20July%2030%2C%20ended%20in%20tragedy%20when%20the%20D-21%20collided%20with%20the%20M-21%20after%20release%2C%20destroying%20both%20aircraft.%20Pilot%20Bill%20Park%20and%20Launch%20Control%20Officer%20Ray%20Torrick%20successfully%20ejected%2C%20but%20Torrick's%20flight%20suit%20was%20likely%20torn%20in%20the%20process%2C%20leading%20to%20it%20filling%20with%20water%20when%20both%20men%20landed%20in%20the%20ocean%2C%20causing%20him%20to%20drown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20crash%2C%20it%20was%20decided%20that%20using%20M-21s%20as%20a%20mothership%20was%20too%20dangerous.%20Instead%2C%20a%20modified%20B-52H%20would%20be%20used%2C%20carrying%20up%20to%20two%20drones%20under%20its%20wings.%20As%20the%20bomber%20was%20unable%20to%20fly%20at%20the%20speed%20required%20to%20activate%20the%20D-21's%20scramjet%20engine%2C%20a%2044-foot%20rocket%20booster%20was%20attached%20underneath%20it.%20After%20release%2C%20the%20booster%20would%20ignite%20to%20bring%20the%20D-21%20to%20the%20required%20speed%2C%20then%20detach%20after%20its%20scramjet%20came%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20B-52H%20bomber%20carries%20the%20D-21B.%20A%20rocket%20booster%20provided%20the%20acceleration%20to%20start%20the%20drone's%20ramjet%20engine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661eaa5120b15f0ff42861eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221188%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20B-52H%20bomber%20carries%20the%20D-21B.%20A%20rocket%20booster%20provided%20the%20acceleration%20to%20start%20the%20drone's%20ramjet%20engine.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ESenior%20Bowl%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20dubbed%20Project%20Senior%20Bowl%2C%20the%20new%20system%20was%20tested%20multiple%20times%20between%20September%201967%20and%20early%201969%20with%20mixed%20results.%20The%20D-21's%20first%20fully%20successful%20test%20occurred%20on%20June%2016%2C%201968%2C%20which%20saw%20it%20fly%20some%203%2C000%20miles%20at%2090%2C000%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20its%20spotty%20success%20record%2C%20the%20drone%20was%20approved%20for%20limited%20service%20in%201969.%20Flying%20out%20of%20Andersen%20Air%20Force%20Base%2C%20the%20D-21s%20were%20given%20the%20task%20of%20spying%20on%20China's%20Lop%20Nor%20nuclear%20test%20site%2C%20where%20China%20had%20detonated%20its%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-china-is-rapidly-expanding-its-nuclear-arsenal-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enuclear%20weapon%3C%2Fa%3E%20five%20years%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20the%20tests%20had%20mixed%20results%2C%20the%20missions%20were%20all%20failures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20mission%2C%20on%20November%209%2C%201969%2C%20was%20perhaps%20the%20worst.%20After%20launching%20from%20its%20mothership%20and%20reaching%20Lop%20Nor%2C%20contact%20with%20the%20D-21%20was%20lost%2C%20and%20it%20disappeared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20drone%20continued%20flying%20all%20the%20way%20into%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20and%20crashed%20in%20the%20Siberian%20wilderness.%20With%20the%20wreckage%20recovered%2C%20Soviet%20engineers%20drew%20up%20plans%20for%20a%20reverse-engineered%20copy%20called%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnationalinterest.org%2Fblog%2Fbuzz%2Frussia-got-its-hands-mini-sr-71-mach-3-spy-drone-steal-its-secrets-58302%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVoron%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20the%20project%20was%20never%20pursued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20more%20than%20a%20year%20of%20further%20testing%20and%20preparation%20the%20second%20mission%20was%20flown%20on%20December%2016%2C%201970.%20The%20D-21%20launched%20successfully%2C%20reached%20Lop%20Nor%2C%20took%20its%20photographs%2C%20and%20arrived%20at%20the%20return%20point%2C%20but%20the%20film%20canister's%20parachute%20didn't%20deploy%20properly%20after%20ejection%2C%20and%20it%20was%20lost%20at%20sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20mission%2C%20on%20March%204%2C%201971%2C%20proceeded%20similarly.%20The%20film%20canister's%20parachute%20deployed%20successfully%2C%20but%20the%20JC-130B%20failed%20to%20recover%20it%20before%20it%20splashed%20into%20the%20water.%20A%20Navy%20destroyer%20attempted%20to%20recover%20the%20floating%20canister%2C%20but%20accidentally%20collided%20with%20it%2C%20causing%20it%20to%20sink.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fourth%20and%20final%20mission%20two%20weeks%20later%20was%20a%20complete%20failure%2C%20with%20the%20D-21%20crashing%20into%20China's%20southwestern%20Yunnan%20province%20while%20en%20route%20to%20Lop%20Nor.%20The%20drone%20was%20recovered%20by%20the%20Chinese%2C%20and%20is%20on%20display%20at%20the%20Chinese%20Aviation%20Museum%20in%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Senior%20Bowl%20resulting%20in%20four%20operational%20failures%2C%20and%20with%20each%20drone%20costing%20at%20least%20%242.5%20million%2C%20the%20D-21%20program%20became%20hard%20to%20justify%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20as%20satellites%20were%20becoming%20more%20advanced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20the%20program%20was%20canceled%20in%20July%201971.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%2038%20D-21's%20built%2C%2021%20had%20been%20used%20in%20tests%20or%20operations.%20The%20remaining%20D-21s%20were%20put%20into%20storage%2C%20and%20eventually%20made%20their%20way%20to%20the%20boneyard%20at%20Davis-Monthan%20Air%20Force%20Base%20in%20Tucson%2C%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20crashed%20model%20at%20the%20Chinese%20Aviation%20Museum%2C%2011%20D-21s%20are%20on%20display%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20WZ-8%20reconnaissance%20drone%20is%20on%20display%20at%20the%2013th%20China%20International%20Aviation%20and%20Aerospace%20Exhibition%20on%20September%2028%2C%202021%20in%20Zhuhai%2C%20China.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661ea83a49058e66935686ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20WZ-8%20reconnaissance%20drone%20is%20on%20display%20at%20the%2013th%20China%20International%20Aviation%20and%20Aerospace%20Exhibition%20on%20September%2028%2C%202021%20in%20Zhuhai%2C%20China.%3Cp%3EChen%20Xiao%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20Chinese%20copy%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20D-21%20had%20largely%20faded%20from%20public%20memory%20until%202019%2C%20when%2C%20at%20the%20military%20parade%20commemorating%20the%2070th%20Anniversary%20of%20the%20People's%20Republic%20of%20China%20on%20October%201%2C%20China%20unveiled%20a%20similar-looking%20drone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDubbed%20the%20WZ-8%2C%20the%20drone%20is%20a%20delta-wing%20design%2C%20about%2037%20feet%20long%2C%20and%20has%20a%20wingspan%20of%2022%20feet.%20Instead%20of%20a%20scramjet%20running%20the%20length%20of%20the%20body%2C%20it%20is%20powered%20by%20two%20rocket%20motors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20D-21%2C%20the%20WZ-8%20must%20be%20launched%20by%20a%20mothership%20during%20flight%20%E2%80%94%20specifically%20an%20H-6M%2C%20a%20version%20of%20the%20H-6%20strategic%20bomber%20modified%20to%20carry%20cruise%20missiles%20on%20external%20hardpoints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChinese%20media%20has%20reported%20that%20the%20WZ-8%20is%20capable%20of%20flying%20160%2C000%20feet%20and%20as%20fast%20as%20Mach%206.%20Its%20sensor%20suite%20reportedly%20includes%20a%20daylight%20electro-optical%20sensor%20and%20a%20synthetic%20aperture%20radar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDocuments%20reportedly%20leaked%20from%20US%20intelligence%20sources%20last%20year%20revealed%20that%20China%20has%20%26quot%3Balmost%20certainly%26quot%3B%20established%20its%20first%20operational%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleaked-documents-show-china-plans-for-supersonic-spy-drone-report-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWZ-8%20unit%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20document%2C%20alleged%20to%20originate%20from%20the%20US%20National%20Geospatial-Intelligence%20Agency%2C%20claims%20that%20the%20unit%20is%20based%20at%20Liuan%20Airfield%2C%20and%20that%20its%20missions%20could%20include%20high-altitude%20reconnaissance%20flights%20of%20the%20South%20Korean%20coast%20and%20virtually%20all%20of%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20document%2C%20the%20drone%20would%20be%20released%20from%20its%20mothership%20just%20off%20the%20northern%20or%20eastern%20Chinese%20coast%2C%20execute%20its%20mission%2C%20then%20return%20and%20land%20at%20Chinese%20coastal%20airfields%2C%20whereupon%20it%20would%20be%20loaded%20back%20on%20an%20H-6M%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecent-bomber-flights-reflect-chinas-rapid-military-modernization-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebomber%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20return%20to%20Liuan.%20The%20document%20lists%20the%20WZ-8%20as%20being%20capable%20of%20flying%20up%20to%20100%2C000%20feet%20at%20Mach%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20separately%20speculated%20that%20the%20WZ-8%20could%20be%20used%20to%20track%20US%20carrier%20battle%20groups%20in%20the%20Pacific%20in%20real%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defensenews.com%2Funmanned%2F2023%2F05%2F18%2Fsatellite-image-shows-wz-8-supersonic-drone-at-chinese-base%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESubsequent%20reporting%3C%2Fa%3E%20confirmed%20the%20presence%20of%20at%20least%20one%20WZ-8%20at%20Liuan%20Airfield.%20The%20base%2C%20which%20is%20reportedly%20home%20to%20the%2029th%20Air%20Regiment%20of%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20Air%20Force's%2010th%20Bomber%20Division%2C%20has%20been%20receiving%20extensive%20upgrades%20since%20at%20least%20early%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBenjamin%20Brimelow%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20covering%20international%20military%20and%20defense%20issues.%20He%20holds%20a%20master's%20degree%20in%20Global%20Affairs%20with%20a%20concentration%20in%20international%20security%20from%20the%20Fletcher%20School%20of%20Law%2