Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Findia-meteorological-department-imd-%5C%22%3EIndia%20Meteorological%20Department's%3C%2Fa%3E%20(IMD)%20latest%20forecast%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Findia-likely-to-experience-above-normal-rainfall-this-monsoon-weather-office-5446300%5C%22%3EIndia%20is%20expected%20to%20receive%20above-normal%20rainfall%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20the%20upcoming%20June-September%20southwest%20monsoon%20season.%20This%20is%20great%20news%20after%20a%20gap%20of%20eight%20years%3B%202016%20was%20when%20India%20last%20experienced%20decent%20rain.%20The%20country's%20dependence%20on%20monsoon%20can%20be%20gauged%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20receives%20about%2070-90%25%20of%20its%20annual%20rainfall%20in%20the%20four%20months%20of%20June-September.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENormal%20monsoon%20has%20a%20direct%20impact%20on%20the%20country's%20economy.%20Evenly-distributed%20rainfall%20is%20crucial%20for%20the%2061%25%20of%20Indian%20farmers%20who%20are%20dependent%20on%20monsoon%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Fagriculture%5C%22%3Eagriculture%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20positive%20monsoon%20enhances%20agricultural%20production%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20boosts%20the%20country's%20economy%20and%20enhances%20food%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOveruse%20of%20Groundwater%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20last%20few%20decades%2C%20dwindling%20resources%20have%20led%20to%20overuse%20of%20groundwater.%20According%20to%20the%20Central%20Groundwater%20Board%20of%20India%2C%2018%25%20of%20India's%20groundwater%20assessment%20units%20are%20overexploited%20or%20critical%2C%20meaning%20that%20the%20rate%20at%20which%20water%20is%20extracted%20is%20higher%20than%20the%20rate%20at%20which%20the%20aquifer%20can%20recharge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20overuse%20of%20groundwater%20for%20agriculture%20has%20increased%20since%20the%201960s%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20Green%20Revolution.%20To%20fulfil%20requirements%2C%20a%20largely%20ungoverned%20groundwater%20irrigation%20economy%20has%20mushroomed%20in%20rural%20areas.%20Increased%20availability%20of%20borewells%20and%20free%20or%20subsidised%20electricity%20have%20allowed%20farmers%20to%20withdraw%20groundwater%20at%20will%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20resource's%20overexploitation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20practice%20raises%20concerns%20given%20that%20about%2075%25%20of%20the%20annual%20groundwater%20recharge%20takes%20place%20during%20the%20southwest%20monsoon.%20With%20climate%20change%20altering%20monsoon%20patterns%2C%20these%20recharge%20cycles%20can%20get%20disrupted%2C%20consequently%20leading%20to%20high%20crop%20failures.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBengaluru's%20Mega%20Troubles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMD's%20latest%20monsoon%20prediction%20is%20music%20to%20not%20only%20farmers%20but%20also%20lakhs%20of%20people%20in%20Indian%20cities%20that%20have%20been%20battling%20water-related%20crises.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Fnews%2Fbengaluru-housing-society-residents-announce-poll-boycott-over-water-crisis-775719%5C%22%3EBengaluru%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20foremost%20among%20them%20these%20days.%20It%20has%20two%20major%20sources%20of%20water%20-%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fwill-supply-cauvery-water-to-bengaluru-by-hook-or-by-crook-dk-shivakumar-5470565%5C%22%3ECauvery%20water%3C%2Fa%3E%20takes%20care%20of%2060%25%20of%20the%20city's%20water%20needs%2C%20the%20rest%20is%20fulfilled%20by%20borewells%20handled%20by%20Bengaluru's%20water%20supply%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20large%20lakes%20in%20the%20metropolis%2C%20Varthur%20and%20Bellandur%2C%20have%20been%20lying%20empty%20for%20the%20last%20four%20years%20due%20to%20desilting%20work.%20The%20delay%20in%20their%20rejuvenation%20is%20one%20of%20the%20major%20reasons%20for%20the%20groundwater%20crisis%20in%20Bengaluru.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAbove-normal%20monsoon%20is%20good%20news%20for%20cities%20as%20both%20the%20local%20lakes%20will%20fill%20up%20and%20recharge%20the%20groundwater%20resources.%20The%20Cauvery%20basin%20will%20fill%20up%2C%20benefiting%20the%20south%20Indian%20states%20of%20Karnataka%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%20and%20Kerala%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20S.%20Vishwanath%2C%20trustee%20of%20the%20Biome%20Environmental%20Trust%2C%20Vishwanath%20had%20been%20one%20of%20the%20first%20persons%20to%20launch%20a%20campaign%20for%20rainwater%20harvesting%20in%20the%20city%2C%20way%20back%20in%20the%201990s.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20take%20care%20of%20the%20catchment%20area%20of%20the%20Cauvery%20basin%2C%20especially%20the%20forested%20areas%20of%20Wayanad%2C%20Coorg%20and%20Hassan%2C%20and%20make%20sure%20there%20is%20no%20felling%20of%20trees%20or%20conversion%20of%20land%2C%20no%20sand%20mining%20or%20discharge%20of%20industrial%20effluents%20into%20the%20river.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bangalore%20Water%20Supply%20and%20Sewerage%20Board%20(BWSSB)%2C%20which%20has%20been%20facing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fbangalore-news%2F22-bengaluru-families-fined-for-wasting-drinking-water-amid-severe-shortage-5306908%5C%22%3Esevere%20criticism%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20the%20water%20shortage%20in%20the%20city%2C%20has%20now%20come%20up%20with%20a%20strategy%20to%20conserve%20water%20through%20supply%20cuts%20to%20big%20customers.%20The%20authority%20hopes%20this%20will%20help%20it%20save%20around%2060%20million%20litres%20of%20water%20per%20day%20(MLD).%20%26quot%3BA%2010-20%25%20cut%20is%20manageable%20if%20large%20commercial%20establishments%2C%20apartment%20complexes%20and%20industries%20adopt%20simple%20water%20conservation%20methods%2C%20such%20as%20installing%20aerators%20to%20limit%20tap%20water%20flow%2C%20which%20can%20save%20up%20to%2030%25%20of%20water%20usage%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20%C2%A0BWSSB%20Chairman%20Ram%20Prasath%20Manohar.%20%26quot%3BMany%20large%20establishments%20already%20have%20sewage%20treatment%20plants%20and%20we%20have%20advised%20them%20to%20utilise%20treated%20water%20for%20various%20purposes%2C%20including%20flushing%20and%20gardening.%20The%20BWSSB%20plans%20to%20make%20treated%20water%20available%20to%20households%20through%20pipes%20to%20save%20and%20reuse%20water%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3ENot%20One%20City's%20Crisis%20Alone%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20Bengaluru%2C%20most%20major%20metropolises%20in%20India%20have%20been%20grappling%20with%20water%20shortages%20too.%20Mumbai%2C%20India's%20financial%20capital%2C%20is%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20one.%20The%20water%20stocks%20in%20the%20seven%20lakes%20that%20supply%20water%20to%20Mumbai%20have%20dipped%20to%2037.9%25%2C%20the%20lowest%20in%20the%20last%20three%20years.%20Reports%20indicate%20that%20lakes%20have%20dried%20up%20much%20faster%20this%20year%20due%20to%20inadequate%20rainfall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDelhi%2C%20too%2C%20faces%20drinking%20water%20shortage%20every%20summer.%20The%20groundwater%20is%20depleted%20and%20the%20Yamuna%2C%20the%20source%20of%20at%20least%2060%25%20of%20water%20supplied%20by%20the%20Delhi%20Jal%20Board%2C%20is%20polluted%20beyond%20redemption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChennai%20has%20been%20infamous%20for%20its%20water%20problems%20for%20a%20few%20years%20now.%20The%20supply%20is%20completely%20dependent%20on%20annual%20rainfall.%20As%20with%20other%20cities%2C%20massive%20urbanisation%20and%20industrialisation%20have%20led%20to%20extreme%20weather%20conditions%2C%20triggering%20both%20floods%20and%20droughts.%20In%202015%2C%20it%20witnessed%20heavy%20flooding%20due%20to%20rainfall%2C%20and%20just%20four%20years%20later%2C%20on%20June%2019%2C%202019%2C%20Chennai%20became%20one%20of%20the%20first%20major%20cities%20in%20the%20world%20to%20run%20out%20of%20water%2C%20forcing%20the%20state%20government%20to%20transport%2010%20million%20litres%20of%20water%20a%20day%20to%20its%20citizens.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20rainwater%20in%20the%20city%20is%20let%20off%20into%20the%20sea%20instead%20of%20being%20utilised%20for%20charging%20depleted%20groundwater%20reserves.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20citizen%20has%20to%20participate%20in%20rainwater%20harvesting.%20Otherwise%2C%20even%20a%20bountiful%20monsoon%20gets%20wasted%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Vishwanath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Water%20Tanker%20Economy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20water%20crises%20are%20almost%20permanent%20features%20of%20India's%20urban%20centres%2C%20extending%20much%20beyond%20just%20summers.%20To%20ease%20supply%20gaps%2C%20municipal%20corporations%20and%20citizens%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20turn%20to%20water%20tankers%2C%20which%20have%20become%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20unorganised%20urban%20water%20supply%20chain.%20According%20to%20estimates%2C%20a%20fleet%20of%20over%201%2C500%20water%20tankers%20owned%20by%20around%20500%20dealers%20ply%20the%20length%20and%20breadth%20of%20Bengaluru%20every%20day%2C%20supplying%20water%20to%20various%20localities%2C%20society%20complexes%2C%20and%20businesses.%20However%2C%20this%20is%20an%20unregulated%20economy%2C%20and%20these%20tankers%20draw%20water%20from%20various%20sources%2C%20including%20unsafe%20and%20contaminated%20borewells%20near%20lakes%2C%20agricultural%20lands%2C%20private%20residences%2C%20stormwater%20drains%2C%20and%20even%20burial%20grounds.%20Naturally%2C%20the%20risk%20of%20diseases%20like%20cholera%2C%20jaundice%20and%20E.%20Coli%20infections%20has%20grown%20multifold.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20needs%20a%20countrywide%20law%20to%20regulate%20groundwater%20and%20manage%20freshwater%20resources.%20A%20robust%20civic%20administration%20framework%2C%20with%20Central%20and%20state%20governments%20discharging%20their%20responsibility%20of%20providing%20efficient%20governance%2C%20is%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour.%20%C2%A0Overdependence%20on%20monsoons%20should%20have%20been%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past%20by%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bharti%20Mishra%20Nath%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713589140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Flids04r8_bengaluru-water-afp_625x300_15_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-good-monsoon-forecast-is-a-relief-but-theres-a-much-deeper-problem-5482381%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20needs%20a%20countrywide%20law%20to%20regulate%20groundwater%20and%20manage%20freshwater%20resources.%20Overdependence%20on%20monsoons%20should%20have%20been%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past%20by%20now.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-good-monsoon-forecast-is-a-relief-but-theres-a-much-deeper-problem-5482381%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-good-monsoon-forecast-is-a-relief-but-theres-a-much-deeper-problem-5482381%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findias-good-monsoon-forecast-is-a-relief-but-theres-a-much-deeper-problem-5482381%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Venezuelan%20opposition%20unites%20behind%20Edmundo%20Gonzalez%20as%20presidential%20challenger%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713589086000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109452439%2Cimgsize-1222601.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Frest-of-world%2Fvenezuelan-opposition-unites-behind-edmundo-gonzalez-as-presidential-challeng